What are Biofertilizers?
Biofertilizers are microbial inoculants that harness living microorganisms to enhance soil fertility and promote plant growth by increasing the supply and availability of primary nutrients to the host plant. They colonize the rhizosphere or the interior of the plant and make essential nutrients like nitrogen, phosphorus, and potassium more accessible through natural processes such as nitrogen fixation and phosphate solubilization, offering a sustainable alternative to synthetic chemical fertilizers.
